Chapter 3: Emergent Cosmology and Falsifiability
3.1 Spacetime Emergence and Bounce
In the Quantum Spectral Standard Model (QSSM), the geometry of spacetime is not fundamental but emerges from the collective dynamics of the Group Field Theory (GFT) fields. Spacetime arises as a hydrodynamic condensate of the GFT field \varphi into a coherent state |\psi\rangle.
The effective dynamics of this condensate, described by a Gross–Pitaevskii–like equation for the condensate amplitude, replace the classical Big Bang singularity with a quantum bounce. This resolution avoids the fundamental breakdown of physics that occurs at the Big Bang singularity in classical General Relativity.
